narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I learned a lot about ethical issues in both academia and job market.
Knowledge on the foundations of ethics.
The ethics on job searching and research. What to expect in the American job market.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: I think this course is good enough.
Strength is that it is easy and presents little difficulty in succeeding in the course. It can be improved by reducing the duration of the course through compression.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes. First of all, this is a required course, everyone has to it. Secondly, I think even though everyone has a sense of what is wrong and what is right, but our ideas are not entirely the same. We have to take this course to modify our ideas toward ethical issues.
No, this is a specific course for only specific students.
yes, always good to learn about computer ethics
